The asterisk (*) represents the reaction surfaces in the models NiCoP (111), CoP (011), and NiCoP (111) | CoP (011). “*N2H4” “*N2H3” “*N2H3” “*N2H3” “*N2H3” “*NH2” “*NH” “*N” denote the models with the corresponding adsorbed intermediates residing on the reaction surfaces. The Gibbs free energy diagrams of intermediates were calculated based on computational normal hydrogen electrode (NHE) model proposed by Norskov et al.55. For each elementary step, ΔG was evaluated by the following equation:ΔG=ΔE+ΔZPE−TΔS+ΔGU+ΔGpH+ΔGfield\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
